href="karlcrary.xml"
type="local"
addr="karlcrary">Karl Crary</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Dear friends,</fr:p><fr:p>I am delighted to announce that <fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jonathan Sterling</fr:link> has been selected as the winner of the 2022 Edmund M. Clarke Dissertation Award in CSD for his thesis:</fr:p><fr:p><fr:link
href="sterling-2021-thesis.xml"
type="local"
addr="sterling-2021-thesis">First Steps in Synthetic Tait Computability</fr:link>, October 2021</fr:p><fr:p><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jonathan</fr:link>’s PhD research was advised by <fr:link
href="robertharper.xml"
type="local"
addr="robertharper">Robert Harper</fr:link>.</fr:p><fr:p>This award, endowed by a generous contribution from Professor Ed Clarke and his wife Martha, is given annually to an outstanding dissertation in the Computer Science Department.</fr:p><fr:p>Congratulations <fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jonathan</fr:link>!</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
