href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-008L</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>From September 2023, I am an <fr:link
href="https://www.cst.cam.ac.uk/people/js2878"
type="external"><fr:em>Associate Professor in Logical Foundations and Formal Methods</fr:em></fr:link> at University of Cambridge.</fr:p><fr:p>From 2022, I was a <fr:link
href="jms-0061.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-0061">Marie Skłodowska-Curie Postdoctoral Fellow</fr:link> hosted at <fr:link
href="jms-00GC.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00GC">Aarhus University</fr:link> working with <fr:link
href="larsbirkedal.xml"
type="local"
addr="larsbirkedal">Professor Lars Birkedal</fr:link>.</fr:p><fr:p>From 2016 to 2021, I was a PhD student of <fr:link
href="robertharper.xml"
type="local"
addr="robertharper">Professor Robert Harper</fr:link> at <fr:link
href="cmu.xml"
type="local"
addr="cmu">Carnegie Mellon University</fr:link>, where I wrote my <fr:link
href="sterling-2021-thesis.xml"
type="local"
addr="sterling-2021-thesis">doctoral thesis</fr:link> on <fr:link
href="jms-005T.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-005T">synthetic Tait computability</fr:link> and its application to <fr:link
href="sterling-angiuli-2021.xml"
type="local"
addr="sterling-angiuli-2021">normalization for cubical type theory</fr:link>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
